# Canonical directory card template (do not reinvent)

When adding or modifying any “card” UI (course cards, certificate program cards, blog cards, university program cards, directory grids), **reuse the existing shared card system** instead of creating new bespoke card CSS.

## Source of truth

- **Global styles** live in `src/layouts/Layout.astro` under “Directory card base styles (shared across pages/components)”.
- **Canonical markup** is:
  - `<article class="card card--has-overlay">`
  - `<a class="card-cover" ...>` as the stretch-link
  - `<div class="card-front">` wrapping:
    - `<div class="card-image"> ... </div>`
    - `<div class="card-body"> ... </div>`

## Required sizing/layout rules

- **Image height**: `200px` via `.card-image`
- **Consistent vertical rhythm**: `.card-body` padding and `.card-excerpt` line clamp should remain consistent
- **Full-height cards**: the card must be `height: 100%` so grid rows align

## Color consistency (avoid “random blues”)

- Never hardcode accent blues like `#2563eb` for card borders/labels/CTAs.
- Use theme tokens:
  - `var(--color-primary)` and `var(--color-primary-dark)` for interactive states
  - neutrals from `--neutral-*` for borders/text where appropriate

## Accessibility + linking rules

- Use the overlay link (`.card-cover`) so the whole card is clickable.
- Keep any inline links that must remain clickable **above** the overlay via the existing `.card--has-overlay` pointer-events pattern.

## If a change is needed

- Prefer updating **the shared `.card` styles** once in `src/layouts/Layout.astro` rather than per-component CSS.
- Keep new variants minimal (e.g., add a small modifier class) and document why.
